## Objectives
•	Discover live hosts on a network.
•	Perform TCP port scanning.
•	Identify running services and their versions.
•	Detect the operating system of target machines.
•	Save scan results for documentation and analysis.
•	Understand the fundamentals of network reconnaissance in a controlled environment.

## Lab Environment
•	Attacker Machine: Kali Linux
•	Target Machines: Ubuntu Server / Windows 10
•	Virtualization Platform: VirtualBox
•	Network Type: Host-Only Adapter (or Internal Network)
•	Scanning Tool: Nmap

## Tools Used
•	Nmap
•	Kali Linux
•	VirtualBox
•	Ubuntu Server
•	Windows 7
•	Linux Terminal

## Nmap Commands Used
nmap -sn 192.168.56.0/24
nmap 192.168.56.102
