## Project Workflow
1.	Set up a virtual network using VirtualBox.
2.	Configure Kali Linux as the scanning machine.
3.	Configure Ubuntu/Windows as target systems.
4.	Verify network connectivity between virtual machines.
5.	Perform host discovery using Nmap.
6.	Scan for open TCP ports.
7.	Detect running services and their versions.
8.	Identify the operating system.
9.	Save scan results in multiple formats.
10.	Document findings with screenshots and reports.

________________________________________
Step 1: Install Software
Download and install:
•	VirtualBox
•	Kali Linux
•	Ubuntu Desktop
•	Windows 10 (optional evaluation VM)
________________________________________
Step 2: Create Virtual Machines
Create three VMs.
VM	Purpose
Kali Linux	Attacker
Ubuntu	Target 1
Windows	Target 2
RAM
•	Kali → 4 GB
•	Ubuntu → 2 GB
•	Windows → 4 GB
________________________________________
Step 3: Configure Network
Open
VirtualBox → Settings → Network
Select
Host-Only Adapter
or
Internal Network
All VMs must be on the same network.
Example
Kali
192.168.56.101
Ubuntu
192.168.56.102
Windows
192.168.56.103
Verify connectivity
ping 192.168.56.102
________________________________________
Step 4: Install Services on Ubuntu
Install SSH
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openssh-server
Install Apache
sudo apt install apache2
Start services
sudo systemctl start ssh
sudo systemctl start apache2
________________________________________
Step 5: Verify Services
On Ubuntu
ip a
Find the IP address.
________________________________________
Step 6: Open Kali Terminal
Check Nmap version
nmap --version
